    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Spring Removal and Installation</title>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>All vehicles are equipped with gas-pressurized shock absorbers which will extend unassisted. Do
                    not apply heat or flame to the shock absorbers during removal or component servicing.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Suspension fasteners are critical parts because they affect performance of vital parts and systems
                    and their failure can result in major service expense. A new part with the same part number must be
                    installed if installation becomes necessary. Do not use a replacement part of lesser quality or
                    substitute design. Torque values must be used as specified during reassembly to make sure of correct
                    retention of these parts.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the wheel and tire assembly. For additional information, refer to
                <exhotlnk document="../S17/S17002.htm" bookname="S17002">Wheels and Tires in S17002</exhotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a suitable jack, support the front axle assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the lower shock absorber nut, washers and bolt.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten 353 Nm (260 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401055" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020407.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front spring hanger nut and bolt.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 246 Nm (181 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401056" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020410.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front spring shackle nut and bolt.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 125 Nm (92 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401057" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020411.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If equipped, remove the spring insulator and retain for reuse.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401058" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figdf1/DF1197A.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the 4 U-bolt nuts, washers and the 2 U-bolts.</para>
            <para>&#8226; To install, tighten to 380 Nm (280 Lbf-ft).</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0401059" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../fign00/N0020396.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px"/>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spring.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To install, reverse the removal procedure.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
